# Repository Structure

Organize code by **pipeline stage**, matching the actual codebase.

```
/configs
  /filtering           # deberta_filter.yaml — model hyperparams
  /experiments         # filter_training.yaml, ablations.yaml, asqa_baseline.yaml
  /rag                 # optional RAG pipeline YAML
/src
  /rag_filtering       # Reusable library (thesis code lives here)
    /config            # YAML loader (repo-root configs/)
    /data              # ASQALoader
    /rag               # RAGSystem, retrieval, training (baseline support)
    /filtering         # Answer quality filtering (CORE THESIS FOCUS)
    /evaluation        # RAGAS + retriever evaluators
    /utils             # Model cache
/data
  /asqa                # labeled_asqa.csv (primary dataset)
/models                # Saved checkpoints
/results               # Experiment outputs
/scripts               # Headless CLI runners
/notebooks             # Thin experiment/reporting notebooks (01–05)
/experiments           # Side experiments (e.g. self_rag_verifier)
/tests                 # Unit tests
```

## Pipeline Flow

```
retrieve → generate → filter (answer quality) → accept/reject
```

- Filtering operates AFTER generation. Retrieval is assumed correct;
  the filter verifies whether the generated answer is faithful to the
  retrieved context. Interface: `(context, answer)` (NLI-style:
  premise = context, hypothesis = answer).
- Core logic lives in `/src/rag_filtering/`, never in notebooks.
- Notebooks import `rag_filtering` and display results only.
- Configs live in top-level `/configs/`, loaded via `rag_filtering.config.loader`.
- Scripts in `/scripts/` are reproducible headless entry points.
